1
00:00:03,000 --> 00:00:05,799
(Previously)
Stop being sulky. Smile a little.

2
00:00:05,800 --> 00:00:08,700
Whatever you are thinking,
please stop right there.

3
00:00:08,800 --> 00:00:14,000
We are servants. All we can do
is revere him, as our royal master.

4
00:00:14,206 --> 00:00:17,406
I saw Your Highness talking congenially
with the young lady. Do you like her?

5
00:00:17,500 --> 00:00:20,999
Father wants you to get engaged to Lady
Siri... even though you knew I like her too!

6
00:00:21,000 --> 00:00:22,800
What is the name of
that beautiful merchant?

7
00:00:22,900 --> 00:00:25,800
- Saijai!
- She sent some snacks for you.

8
00:00:35,200 --> 00:00:37,700
Who are they?
What are they doing in the back?

9
00:01:59,200 --> 00:02:05,200
"The Edge of Horizon"
(Episode 2)

10
00:02:32,000 --> 00:02:34,402
Who are they?
What are they doing in the back?

11
00:02:35,162 --> 00:02:36,163
Your Highness?

12
00:02:38,248 --> 00:02:39,249
Phob?

13
00:02:41,533 --> 00:02:42,786
Hey! Tin!

14
00:02:43,309 --> 00:02:44,250
Tin!

15
00:02:44,285 --> 00:02:45,802
How did you take care of him?

16
00:02:45,842 --> 00:02:47,072
Why did you let him get drunk like this?

17
00:02:47,096 --> 00:02:49,562
You're such a big waste, you servant!

18
00:02:54,840 --> 00:02:56,442
Tin! Tin!

19
00:02:58,890 --> 00:03:00,850
You need to take your master
back home right now.

20
00:03:01,562 --> 00:03:03,962
And I will tell on you to my dad
that you took him to drink.

21
00:03:05,168 --> 00:03:06,408
Go! Just go!

22
00:03:16,848 --> 00:03:17,948
Bring him here. Hurry up!

23
00:03:18,265 --> 00:03:20,122
Watch out! Don't fall!

24
00:03:21,714 --> 00:03:22,715
Here.

25
00:03:29,493 --> 00:03:30,682
Oh my!

26
00:03:31,072 --> 00:03:33,602
Why are you so drunk like this?

27
00:03:33,669 --> 00:03:34,882
Why, Tin?

28
00:03:35,984 --> 00:03:36,985
Oh, you poor thing.

29
00:03:38,010 --> 00:03:39,730
You're done here, you should take a shower.

30
00:03:40,037 --> 00:03:41,442
I will take care of him.

31
00:03:42,335 --> 00:03:43,336
Let's go.

32
00:03:43,935 --> 00:03:44,936
What?

33
00:03:45,701 --> 00:03:48,202
Why don't you let your
son take care of him?

34
00:03:48,546 --> 00:03:51,402
That's right. He can help him get changed.

35
00:03:51,592 --> 00:03:54,962
- You're a woman, you can't do it.
- That's right.

36
00:03:55,213 --> 00:03:57,322
- But…
- You should go. Come on.

37
00:03:58,542 --> 00:04:01,656
Phob, take care of him, okay?

38
00:04:02,162 --> 00:04:03,163
We should go.

39
00:04:05,144 --> 00:04:06,802
Nual? Come on.

40
00:04:08,637 --> 00:04:11,642
Phob, you need to clean him well.

41
00:04:12,394 --> 00:04:13,395
Let's go.

42
00:08:58,808 --> 00:09:00,842
♪ The sun ♪

43
00:09:01,325 --> 00:09:04,362
♪ and the ground are far away. ♪

44
00:09:06,368 --> 00:09:08,282
♪ They are too far apart ♪

45
00:09:09,042 --> 00:09:13,522
♪ and they are unreachable. ♪

46
00:09:13,754 --> 00:09:15,562
♪ Even they are destined ♪

47
00:09:16,322 --> 00:09:20,642
♪ not to be together, ♪

48
00:09:21,562 --> 00:09:26,002
♪ I don't believe that I could
only have you in my dream. ♪

49
00:09:28,272 --> 00:09:30,322
♪ Will it be possible ♪

50
00:09:30,389 --> 00:09:33,842
♪ for us to be in love? ♪

51
00:09:34,096 --> 00:09:36,042
♪ It seems so far away ♪

52
00:09:36,097 --> 00:09:39,682
♪ that we couldn't see the end. ♪

53
00:09:40,482 --> 00:09:42,922
♪ I won't have a change of heart. ♪

54
00:09:42,942 --> 00:09:45,162
♪ It's just like the sun ♪

55
00:09:45,248 --> 00:09:48,642
♪ that got to meet the ground at dawn. ♪

56
00:09:48,883 --> 00:09:52,075
♪ It was a brief moment but ♪

57
00:09:54,322 --> 00:09:56,402
♪ I will wait to see ♪

58
00:09:56,642 --> 00:09:59,562
♪ the first light of the day. ♪

59
00:10:15,549 --> 00:10:16,550
Phob!

60
00:10:18,219 --> 00:10:21,088
You shouldn't have taken
him to go partying this late.

61
00:10:22,322 --> 00:10:23,562
I tried to stop him.

62
00:10:23,848 --> 00:10:24,849
Stop talking back to me.

63
00:10:28,520 --> 00:10:29,642
You need to pack up.

64
00:10:29,899 --> 00:10:32,435
You need to visit your aunt in Ayutthaya
with me in two days.

65
00:12:07,344 --> 00:12:08,345
Phob.

66
00:12:14,154 --> 00:12:17,002
Nual said that you will visit
your relatives in Ayutthaya, right?

67
00:12:18,437 --> 00:12:19,557
That's right, Your Highness.

68
00:12:20,522 --> 00:12:21,842
For how many days?

69
00:12:23,141 --> 00:12:25,722
A few days, I guess.

70
00:12:34,802 --> 00:12:37,642
- About last night…
- If there is nothing else,

71
00:12:38,018 --> 00:12:39,882
I really need to pack
my stuff, Your Highness.

72
00:12:40,525 --> 00:12:41,526
Phob!

73
00:12:42,442 --> 00:12:43,443
I…

74
00:12:43,548 --> 00:12:44,788
There you are.

75
00:12:48,568 --> 00:12:49,569
Actually,

76
00:12:50,056 --> 00:12:51,762
Princess Ruethaisiri is here to see you.

77
00:12:52,440 --> 00:12:54,080
She is talking to your grandma right now.

78
00:12:55,165 --> 00:12:56,166
Got it.

79
00:13:15,818 --> 00:13:18,522
Ruethaisiri just learned how to bake a cake

80
00:13:18,546 --> 00:13:20,234
and she's kind enough to share some with us.

81
00:13:22,608 --> 00:13:24,288
You should try, honey.

82
00:13:25,262 --> 00:13:27,422
Please come and sit with me.

83
00:13:30,368 --> 00:13:31,842
Thank you so much.

84
00:13:32,802 --> 00:13:33,948
Oh my goodness,

85
00:13:34,250 --> 00:13:36,562
the cake looks so good

86
00:13:37,353 --> 00:13:39,281
just like the giver.

87
00:13:39,953 --> 00:13:42,922
It's just like a match made in heaven.

88
00:13:44,592 --> 00:13:47,122
Stop talking already, come on.

89
00:13:54,848 --> 00:13:57,042
You don't want to marry me, do you?

90
00:13:59,941 --> 00:14:02,962
Why did you bring it up?

91
00:14:04,442 --> 00:14:07,362
You've changed
since you heard about our engagement.

92
00:14:08,429 --> 00:14:10,682
It seems like you're not
comfortable talking to me.

93
00:14:12,781 --> 00:14:13,782
I…

94
00:14:13,912 --> 00:14:15,442
I still like you the same.

95
00:14:16,762 --> 00:14:17,763
But…

96
00:14:18,021 --> 00:14:20,282
- I just...
- You were forced, weren't you?

97
00:14:26,522 --> 00:14:28,802
I see you as a sister.

98
00:14:29,807 --> 00:14:32,442
When I learned that we needed
to get married, I was shocked.

99
00:14:33,794 --> 00:14:35,002
I understand you completely.

100
00:14:35,581 --> 00:14:37,442
We're the 'suitable' couple.

101
00:14:38,652 --> 00:14:41,242
My dad chose my whole entire life.

102
00:14:42,795 --> 00:14:44,875
If we didn’t come with titles,

103
00:14:45,118 --> 00:14:47,835
perhaps we could have
more freedom in our lives.

104
00:14:49,453 --> 00:14:52,222
You don't want to get married either?

105
00:14:53,968 --> 00:14:55,448
Can we say no to our parents?

106
00:14:57,777 --> 00:14:58,778
What about this?

107
00:14:59,472 --> 00:15:01,242
I will ask my father

108
00:15:01,344 --> 00:15:02,722
to postpone the wedding.

109
00:15:03,612 --> 00:15:04,982
When I come back from the UK,

110
00:15:05,006 --> 00:15:06,715
we can talk about it again.

111
00:15:07,214 --> 00:15:09,475
We should be grown enough by then,

112
00:15:10,241 --> 00:15:12,182
and we need to be firm
when we tell our parents

113
00:15:12,206 --> 00:15:14,166
that we don't like each other like that.

114
00:15:15,042 --> 00:15:17,722
I think our fathers should understand.

115
00:15:19,322 --> 00:15:20,323
Good idea.

116
00:16:02,562 --> 00:16:04,563
[We need to talk.]

117
00:16:27,514 --> 00:16:28,653
You called me here,

118
00:16:29,954 --> 00:16:31,362
what can I do for you?

119
00:16:34,199 --> 00:16:35,200
We need to talk.

120
00:16:38,448 --> 00:16:39,449
Can we talk tomorrow?

121
00:16:40,651 --> 00:16:41,652
It's getting late

122
00:16:42,995 --> 00:16:43,996
and it is inappropriate.

123
00:16:45,573 --> 00:16:47,402
What do you mean by 'inappropriate'?

124
00:16:49,171 --> 00:16:51,211
We used to sneak out
here to hang out all the time.

125
00:16:53,452 --> 00:16:54,582
That was before this.

126
00:16:57,904 --> 00:16:58,905
Right now,

127
00:17:00,562 --> 00:17:01,682
it is not the same anymore.

128
00:17:03,162 --> 00:17:04,242
What is not the same?

129
00:17:06,466 --> 00:17:07,602
I am still the same.

130
00:17:12,773 --> 00:17:14,242
Is it you

131
00:17:15,348 --> 00:17:16,349
who has changed?

132
00:17:23,152 --> 00:17:24,415
At the bar last night,

133
00:17:25,112 --> 00:17:27,113
you still haven't told me

134
00:17:27,142 --> 00:17:28,182
why you tried to avoid me?

135
00:17:31,202 --> 00:17:32,562
Please let it go, don't mind me.

136
00:17:32,802 --> 00:17:33,962
Of course, I do.

137
00:17:35,976 --> 00:17:37,522
Phob, I will leave for the UK soon,

138
00:17:37,730 --> 00:17:40,482
you wish me to leave
when things are unclear like this?

139
00:17:52,112 --> 00:17:53,113
Perhaps,

140
00:17:54,528 --> 00:17:55,882
it is better that way.

141
00:17:59,256 --> 00:18:00,468
Excuse me.

142
00:18:01,045 --> 00:18:02,046
Coward!

143
00:18:06,074 --> 00:18:07,514
You're not Phob that I used to know.

144
00:18:15,661 --> 00:18:16,722
Is this what you want?

145
00:18:21,700 --> 00:18:23,660
You kissed someone and
now you're acting like this.

146
00:18:39,769 --> 00:18:41,049
I know what happened last night.

147
00:18:46,442 --> 00:18:47,843
You kissed me

148
00:18:49,682 --> 00:18:50,683
and I knew it.

149
00:19:23,056 --> 00:19:24,057
I'm sorry.

150
00:19:24,986 --> 00:19:27,522
I'm sorry, it was an accident.

151
00:19:29,002 --> 00:19:30,003
An accident?

152
00:19:31,733 --> 00:19:32,734
What do you mean?

153
00:19:33,685 --> 00:19:35,322
You still haven't told me the truth.

154
00:19:36,304 --> 00:19:37,482
What do you want me to say?

155
00:19:38,453 --> 00:19:40,973
You want me to say that a servant
took advantage of his master?

156
00:19:43,357 --> 00:19:45,122
That I didn't know my place?

157
00:19:46,760 --> 00:19:48,480
That I thought of you in inappropriate way?

158
00:19:49,666 --> 00:19:51,482
So that you can be
disgusted by me even more?

159
00:20:26,594 --> 00:20:28,962
Do you still think that
you're disgusting to me?

160
00:20:35,861 --> 00:20:37,802
♪ The sun ♪

161
00:20:38,538 --> 00:20:41,362
♪ and the ground are far away. ♪

162
00:20:43,522 --> 00:20:45,162
♪ They are too far apart ♪

163
00:20:46,082 --> 00:20:50,322
♪ and they are unreachable. ♪

164
00:20:50,882 --> 00:20:52,542
♪ Even they are destined ♪

165
00:20:53,442 --> 00:20:57,562
♪ not to be together, ♪

166
00:20:58,002 --> 00:20:59,762
I'm not dreaming, am I?

167
00:21:01,502 --> 00:21:02,562
You're dreaming

168
00:21:05,765 --> 00:21:06,842
and you will wake up soon.

169
00:21:17,864 --> 00:21:18,865
If this is a dream,

170
00:21:20,286 --> 00:21:22,082
then I want to stay in my dream forever.

171
00:21:24,800 --> 00:21:26,082
I don't want to wake up.

172
00:21:27,221 --> 00:21:29,402
Then you should keep on dreaming like this.

173
00:21:29,589 --> 00:21:31,762
♪ It seems so far away ♪

174
00:21:32,002 --> 00:21:34,482
♪ that we couldn't see the end. ♪

175
00:21:35,805 --> 00:21:38,162
♪ I won't have a change of heart. ♪

176
00:21:38,242 --> 00:21:40,243
♪ It's just like the sun ♪

177
00:21:40,562 --> 00:21:41,563
But soon

178
00:21:43,802 --> 00:21:44,922
you will study abroad.

179
00:21:47,448 --> 00:21:48,449
So what?

180
00:21:50,382 --> 00:21:54,721
Are you saying that you won't
wait for me while I study in the UK?

181
00:21:59,629 --> 00:22:01,802
I don't care if it will
be months, or years,

182
00:22:02,682 --> 00:22:03,683
or all my life,

183
00:22:06,002 --> 00:22:08,202
I will wait for you and you only.

184
00:22:10,088 --> 00:22:12,208
No matter what,

185
00:22:13,082 --> 00:22:14,083
I will forever

186
00:22:15,121 --> 00:22:16,122
be your Phob.

187
00:22:22,688 --> 00:22:24,122
Aren't you the cutest?

188
00:22:49,458 --> 00:22:50,459
I love you.

189
00:22:53,570 --> 00:22:54,810
I love you, too, Your Highness.

190
00:23:14,162 --> 00:23:16,122
It's late, where have you been?

191
00:23:17,462 --> 00:23:20,075
I couldn't sleep so I went
out to get some fresh air.

192
00:23:46,146 --> 00:23:48,402
We're here to say goodbye, Your Highness.

193
00:23:50,808 --> 00:23:52,922
We will visit our relatives in Ayutthaya

194
00:23:53,053 --> 00:23:54,322
for a couple days.

195
00:23:54,961 --> 00:23:55,962
You should go

196
00:23:56,094 --> 00:23:58,942
and take care of your
relatives until they get better,

197
00:23:59,202 --> 00:24:00,748
then you can come back.

198
00:24:06,205 --> 00:24:09,002
Phob, take this.

199
00:24:19,910 --> 00:24:21,035
Thank you, Your Highness.

200
00:24:21,378 --> 00:24:24,535
You should be gone forever.

201
00:24:26,478 --> 00:24:28,315
You have such a foul mouth.

202
00:24:28,457 --> 00:24:30,742
If you're quiet, nobody
would think that you're a mute.

203
00:24:47,658 --> 00:24:48,659
Let's go, Phob.

204
00:24:54,221 --> 00:24:57,082
I wish you two a safe trip.

205
00:25:26,194 --> 00:25:27,195
Come in.

206
00:25:34,282 --> 00:25:35,283
What is it, Tin?

207
00:25:37,557 --> 00:25:38,558
About…

208
00:25:38,933 --> 00:25:41,146
my study in the UK.

209
00:25:42,837 --> 00:25:44,522
What about it? Is there a problem?

210
00:25:45,762 --> 00:25:47,482
Everything is fine.

211
00:25:49,359 --> 00:25:51,828
But I need to ask you a favor.

212
00:25:55,802 --> 00:25:57,603
Is it possible

213
00:25:58,469 --> 00:26:00,922
that Phob could go to the UK with me?

214
00:26:05,722 --> 00:26:08,362
You two can't be apart, can you?

215
00:26:12,085 --> 00:26:14,181
Actually, I think that

216
00:26:14,608 --> 00:26:15,892
Phob is a bright student.

217
00:26:17,664 --> 00:26:20,565
If any of the departments issue
scholarships to study in the UK,

218
00:26:21,370 --> 00:26:23,442
I think Phob should join the test.

219
00:26:24,053 --> 00:26:25,682
He could be there to take care of you.

220
00:26:28,402 --> 00:26:29,842
Thank you, Dad.

221
00:26:38,776 --> 00:26:40,922
He wanted Phob to go to the UK with him?

222
00:26:49,600 --> 00:26:50,642
What is going on?

223
00:26:51,888 --> 00:26:54,742
Why did you ask Dad to
send Phob to the UK with you?

224
00:26:55,096 --> 00:26:56,322
You should have asked for me.

225
00:26:57,266 --> 00:26:58,267
Oh, come on.

226
00:26:58,696 --> 00:27:02,082
Honestly, you should focus
on passing the tests here first.

227
00:27:04,283 --> 00:27:05,435
Are you underestimating me?

228
00:27:07,947 --> 00:27:09,275
You see him as being better than me?

229
00:27:09,713 --> 00:27:11,581
You only focus on him…

230
00:27:17,682 --> 00:27:18,683
I just figured it out.

231
00:27:20,786 --> 00:27:21,866
What are you talking about?

232
00:27:23,684 --> 00:27:26,202
I saw it the other night

233
00:27:26,962 --> 00:27:28,082
in the back of the bar.

234
00:27:28,733 --> 00:27:29,734
I know what you did.

235
00:27:34,381 --> 00:27:35,882
What did you see?

236
00:27:46,736 --> 00:27:48,522
You were completely drunk.

237
00:27:49,963 --> 00:27:50,924
Right?

238
00:27:50,948 --> 00:27:53,574
So you can Phob can
go partying all the time?

239
00:27:54,482 --> 00:27:55,682
Stop talking nonsense already.

240
00:28:05,149 --> 00:28:06,669
Why did he act so surprised like that?

241
00:28:09,250 --> 00:28:10,482
They're so weird.

242
00:28:20,082 --> 00:28:21,083
[Ayutthaya]

243
00:28:25,992 --> 00:28:27,442
Thank you so much, Nual.

244
00:28:27,842 --> 00:28:30,442
Actually, I'm not feeling bad at all.

245
00:28:30,922 --> 00:28:33,522
You and Phob shouldn't
have come all the way here.

246
00:28:34,602 --> 00:28:35,842
It's okay, Cham.

247
00:28:36,202 --> 00:28:38,146
We should be on vacation once in a while.

248
00:28:39,842 --> 00:28:41,602
Well, I need to rest.

249
00:28:42,162 --> 00:28:43,322
Make yourself at home.

250
00:28:54,042 --> 00:28:55,043
Mom?

251
00:28:55,584 --> 00:28:57,242
Aunt Cham looks fine to me.

252
00:28:58,585 --> 00:28:59,842
Should we go back now?

253
00:29:00,669 --> 00:29:02,202
I think we should stay for a while.

254
00:29:02,762 --> 00:29:03,842
We don't need to rush back.

255
00:29:04,173 --> 00:29:05,432
What? Mom!

256
00:29:09,749 --> 00:29:10,922
What are you talking about?

257
00:29:11,504 --> 00:29:13,562
You're moving to Ayutthaya?

258
00:29:13,818 --> 00:29:14,819
Yes, Your Highness.

259
00:29:15,504 --> 00:29:18,362
My relatives can help us.

260
00:29:19,293 --> 00:29:20,294
I think

261
00:29:21,138 --> 00:29:22,722
I will find something to sell

262
00:29:23,224 --> 00:29:25,762
and I can take care of my sick relatives.

263
00:29:27,096 --> 00:29:28,802
Why is it so sudden?

264
00:29:29,298 --> 00:29:30,477
Is everything okay?

265
00:29:30,702 --> 00:29:33,608
That's right. Or you think that

266
00:29:33,882 --> 00:29:36,002
we don't take good care of you?

267
00:29:36,091 --> 00:29:39,368
You can tell me if
something is bothering you.

268
00:29:41,556 --> 00:29:42,916
Everything is fine, Your Highness.

269
00:29:43,605 --> 00:29:45,562
I can be who I am

270
00:29:46,682 --> 00:29:48,037
because of this place.

271
00:29:49,072 --> 00:29:52,173
I don't know how to

272
00:29:53,034 --> 00:29:54,442
pay you back for your kindness.

273
00:29:55,722 --> 00:29:59,162
It's just that I need to take
care of my sick relatives.

274
00:30:00,669 --> 00:30:01,670
And that's all.

275
00:30:07,512 --> 00:30:09,613
Nual? What about Phob?

276
00:30:13,269 --> 00:30:14,802
He will stay with me.

277
00:30:18,176 --> 00:30:19,242
He won't be back.

278
00:30:25,885 --> 00:30:27,800
Nual! Nual!

279
00:30:32,082 --> 00:30:33,162
My dad told me that

280
00:30:33,621 --> 00:30:36,661
he wants Phob to join the test for a
scholarship to study in the UK with me.

281
00:30:37,690 --> 00:30:38,922
Please let him go with me.

282
00:30:43,562 --> 00:30:44,563
Your Highness.

283
00:30:46,344 --> 00:30:47,802
I'm forever grateful

284
00:30:49,242 --> 00:30:51,522
for your kindness to both of us.

285
00:30:52,584 --> 00:30:53,585
But…

286
00:30:54,296 --> 00:30:55,802
Phob has to stay here with me.

287
00:30:57,602 --> 00:30:59,602
You're about to get in the
way of his entire future.

288
00:31:01,293 --> 00:31:03,493
You know that he's a fast
learner and a bright student.

289
00:31:04,472 --> 00:31:07,322
You know that he deserves better education.

290
00:31:07,827 --> 00:31:08,875
I know it well.

291
00:31:12,002 --> 00:31:13,682
But this is the only way…

292
00:31:14,776 --> 00:31:15,802
to protect him

293
00:31:16,760 --> 00:31:17,761
and…

294
00:31:18,542 --> 00:31:20,642
to protect your honor.

295
00:31:22,372 --> 00:31:23,451
What are you talking about?

296
00:31:26,098 --> 00:31:27,099
Who would hurt Phob?

297
00:31:28,434 --> 00:31:31,922
What does my honor
have to do with it?

298
00:31:45,070 --> 00:31:46,322
Your Highness,

299
00:31:47,928 --> 00:31:49,002
please trust me.

300
00:31:52,242 --> 00:31:54,162
This is for the best.

301
00:32:35,029 --> 00:32:37,042
♪ The sun ♪

302
00:32:37,626 --> 00:32:40,602
♪ and the ground are far away. ♪

303
00:32:42,602 --> 00:32:44,562
♪ They are too far apart ♪

304
00:32:47,000 --> 00:32:48,562
- Do you know what it is?
- Like what?

305
00:32:48,984 --> 00:32:49,985
Like Ngoh!

306
00:32:50,802 --> 00:32:53,042
You saw me as an ugly
and dirty-looking guy, didn't you?

307
00:32:53,133 --> 00:32:56,242
I mean you look like Ngoh
when he shows his real self.

308
00:32:57,122 --> 00:32:59,762
Ngoh's skin is covered with gold.

309
00:33:02,997 --> 00:33:04,082
But I'm just a servant,

310
00:33:05,674 --> 00:33:07,062
I am nothing like him.

311
00:33:08,276 --> 00:33:11,242
Nobody would toss me a garland

312
00:33:11,802 --> 00:33:12,803
like she did to him.

313
00:33:13,864 --> 00:33:14,865
No garland

314
00:33:15,437 --> 00:33:17,562
but you can have the cotton rose.

315
00:33:18,962 --> 00:33:20,282
So it means that

316
00:33:23,522 --> 00:33:26,762
you choose me,

317
00:33:36,106 --> 00:33:38,042
Can you help me

318
00:33:38,107 --> 00:33:40,482
- find a rental house in the area?
- Sure.

319
00:33:41,408 --> 00:33:43,409
Are you sure about moving back here?

320
00:33:43,834 --> 00:33:45,562
You're not staying in the palace anymore?

321
00:33:46,416 --> 00:33:48,242
- Or your masters…?
- All of them

322
00:33:48,266 --> 00:33:49,867
are so kind to me and my son.

323
00:33:50,581 --> 00:33:51,582
That's why

324
00:33:52,112 --> 00:33:54,162
we shouldn't go back there.

325
00:33:55,506 --> 00:33:56,507
What did you just say?

326
00:33:57,538 --> 00:33:58,938
We're not going back to the palace?

327
00:34:09,608 --> 00:34:11,362
Mom! Mom!

328
00:34:12,482 --> 00:34:14,602
What do you mean by us
not going back to the palace?

329
00:34:14,922 --> 00:34:17,402
You heard what I
said. We will stay here.

330
00:34:17,736 --> 00:34:19,802
- You can't go back.
- Why is that?

331
00:34:20,082 --> 00:34:21,320
You should ask yourself that.

332
00:34:21,704 --> 00:34:22,705
What did I do?

333
00:34:29,506 --> 00:34:31,122
That night, under a cotton rose tree,

334
00:34:32,530 --> 00:34:33,731
I saw you

335
00:34:35,602 --> 00:34:36,762
and Prince Tinnakorn.

336
00:34:43,546 --> 00:34:44,547
If you saw us,

337
00:34:45,314 --> 00:34:46,402
then you would know

338
00:34:47,554 --> 00:34:49,542
that we shared the same feeling.

339
00:34:50,285 --> 00:34:52,322
Why do you have to stop
people who are in love?

340
00:34:52,591 --> 00:34:55,602
Did you hear what you just said?

341
00:34:55,626 --> 00:34:56,690
It is the truth.

342
00:34:57,482 --> 00:34:58,722
I am speaking the truth.

343
00:34:59,602 --> 00:35:02,962
The prince and I, we are in love.

344
00:35:04,048 --> 00:35:05,968
You can't love him like that.

345
00:35:09,395 --> 00:35:11,528
You should revere him.

346
00:35:12,075 --> 00:35:14,515
- Because he is your master.
- So what?

347
00:35:15,158 --> 00:35:16,802
I can revere him

348
00:35:17,525 --> 00:35:19,922
and let him be my lover. Can't I do that?

349
00:35:19,952 --> 00:35:22,842
- You're about to ruin his reputation.
- Ruin because of what?

350
00:35:23,733 --> 00:35:25,402
Because I am a man?

351
00:35:25,578 --> 00:35:27,642
Or because I am a servant
and he is my master?

352
00:35:27,689 --> 00:35:28,985
Both of those reasons!

353
00:35:30,298 --> 00:35:31,762
You should know

354
00:35:32,389 --> 00:35:34,202
that the sky is high and the ground is low.

355
00:35:34,888 --> 00:35:37,282
You shouldn't drag the sky to stoop
to ground level.

356
00:35:39,828 --> 00:35:40,829
Mom,

357
00:35:42,102 --> 00:35:45,192
there is no high or low in love.

358
00:35:45,720 --> 00:35:47,242
It is about our hearts.

359
00:35:50,802 --> 00:35:52,402
If the sky and the ground got in my way,

360
00:35:52,728 --> 00:35:54,762
if a master and a
servant got in my way,

361
00:35:55,240 --> 00:35:56,882
I will destroy them all.

362
00:36:24,162 --> 00:36:25,163
Phob!

363
00:36:27,880 --> 00:36:28,881
Phob!

364
00:36:31,802 --> 00:36:32,803
Phob!

365
00:36:34,322 --> 00:36:35,842
Phob! Come back here.

366
00:37:35,384 --> 00:37:36,385
Phob!

367
00:37:59,178 --> 00:38:01,562
Co..Colo…

368
00:38:02,597 --> 00:38:04,522
nel…means...

369
00:38:06,410 --> 00:38:07,970
a senior commissioned military officer.

370
00:38:13,514 --> 00:38:14,515
Did I get it right?

371
00:38:18,493 --> 00:38:22,242
Damn it! I pronounced it wrong.

372
00:38:22,694 --> 00:38:25,602
Why is it written one way and said another?

373
00:38:28,258 --> 00:38:29,698
Damn you rain! Stop raining already.

374
00:38:37,542 --> 00:38:38,543
Is that…

375
00:38:39,165 --> 00:38:40,166
Phob?

376
00:38:42,728 --> 00:38:43,729
Tin?

377
00:38:53,618 --> 00:38:54,619
Where are you going?

378
00:39:04,678 --> 00:39:06,602
Didn't I tell you to study?

379
00:39:07,010 --> 00:39:08,754
I just saw Phob

380
00:39:09,282 --> 00:39:10,882
and Tin running to the main quarters.

381
00:39:11,316 --> 00:39:13,876
- So I was about to…
- You need to go back to your room to study.

382
00:39:41,589 --> 00:39:42,590
Phob!

383
00:39:44,133 --> 00:39:45,853
I thought that I would never see you again.

384
00:39:47,542 --> 00:39:48,802
What happened?

385
00:39:48,906 --> 00:39:50,642
Why did both of you need to move out?

386
00:39:51,607 --> 00:39:52,642
I don't get it.

387
00:39:54,242 --> 00:39:55,243
Your Highness,

388
00:39:57,282 --> 00:39:58,322
my mom found out about it.

389
00:39:59,978 --> 00:40:01,242
She knows about us.

390
00:40:01,642 --> 00:40:02,643
What did you just say?

391
00:40:06,828 --> 00:40:09,429
Is that the reason why she
wanted you to move out?

392
00:40:11,562 --> 00:40:13,242
What should we do?

393
00:40:17,456 --> 00:40:18,802
Don't you worry.

394
00:40:20,466 --> 00:40:23,748
I will not let anything to get in our way.

395
00:40:24,908 --> 00:40:26,268
I will not give up

396
00:40:27,578 --> 00:40:29,082
and you can't give up either.

397
00:40:34,634 --> 00:40:37,072
Phob, I talked to my dad
about going to the UK.

398
00:40:38,128 --> 00:40:40,648
He said that you can join the
scholarship's test and follow me.

399
00:40:41,642 --> 00:40:43,562
If you pass the test, you will join me.

400
00:40:44,722 --> 00:40:45,882
We can study abroad together.

401
00:40:46,562 --> 00:40:48,482
- Really?
- Yeah.

402
00:40:49,522 --> 00:40:50,562
We will go there together.

403
00:41:03,317 --> 00:41:04,318
Phob,

404
00:41:05,475 --> 00:41:07,315
you're soaking wet.

405
00:41:07,882 --> 00:41:09,162
I think you should get changed.

406
00:41:10,240 --> 00:41:12,802
And I will bring you to
see my dad tomorrow.

407
00:41:13,308 --> 00:41:14,908
He will talk to Nual for you.

408
00:41:15,562 --> 00:41:17,362
I don't think Nual would disagree with him.

409
00:41:23,799 --> 00:41:24,800
What is it?

410
00:41:26,317 --> 00:41:27,318
You know what?

411
00:41:28,696 --> 00:41:30,416
I thought that I would never see you again.

412
00:41:33,141 --> 00:41:35,642
Well, you're seeing me now.

413
00:41:37,130 --> 00:41:38,482
Are you still not satisfied?

414
00:41:43,383 --> 00:41:45,201
What if I say that I'm not satisfied yet?

415
00:41:50,269 --> 00:41:53,202
So what do you want me to do?

416
00:41:53,270 --> 00:41:54,271
To satisfy you?

417
00:45:30,888 --> 00:45:33,362
It's late and it's pouring rain.

418
00:45:33,882 --> 00:45:34,883
What are they doing?

419
00:45:35,720 --> 00:45:36,882
Where are you going?

420
00:45:39,608 --> 00:45:40,682
Dad?

421
00:45:44,242 --> 00:45:45,322
What are you doing here?

422
00:45:46,194 --> 00:45:48,082
I really saw Phob.

423
00:45:48,349 --> 00:45:50,642
Tin is with him, too.
I don't know what they are up to.

424
00:45:52,242 --> 00:45:54,002
Are you going back to study? Nicely?

425
00:45:55,000 --> 00:45:56,001
But Dad?

426
00:45:58,448 --> 00:45:59,449
Yes.

427
00:46:40,313 --> 00:46:41,314
Your Highness!

428
00:46:41,542 --> 00:46:42,543
Dad!

429
00:47:05,200 --> 00:47:07,499
(Next Episode) The matter between
me and Phob ended that night.

430
00:47:07,500 --> 00:47:10,199
I trust you, Tin, but I don't trust others.

431
00:47:10,200 --> 00:47:12,399
Hey! Stop this! Siam will surely be ruined!

432
00:47:12,400 --> 00:47:15,699
People have started to question
who this government is really ruling for.

433
00:47:15,700 --> 00:47:18,000
You used to live in the
Varakulavadin Palace.

434
00:47:18,700 --> 00:47:21,300
I will execute the plan,
just as I promised there.

435
00:47:21,700 --> 00:47:23,500
That's Phob, Brother Tin.
